This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a St. Patrick's Day celebration at the U.S. Capitol. The President expressed gratitude for the strong relationship between the United States and Ireland, highlighting the contributions of Irish Americans to the nation. He also discussed his conversation with the Taoiseach (Prime Minister) of Ireland about Brexit and expressed confidence that the situation would work out. The President acknowledged the presence of Irish descendants in Congress and his administration, and thanked the Irish delegation for attending the event. He concluded by reaffirming the friendship and partnership between the United States and Ireland.